      "original_classification": "potential-vulnerability",
      "adjusted_severity": "Medium",
      "reviewer_notes": "All 3 gates passed. Gate 1: performUpkeep is a public/exported API declared in IBaseAuction and listed as a named entry point in BUG_BOUNTY_SCOPE.json \u2014 public interface exception applies regardless of internal caller count. Gate 2: attack path depends on price_feeds staleness (SEMI_TRUSTED, in_scope_for_bug_bounty:true); BUG_BOUNTY_SCOPE.json explicitly states staleness within PriceManager logic is in scope. Gate 3: BaseAuction.sol and performUpkeep are explicitly in-scope; the conditional_scope oracle_verification exclusion covers only cryptographic verification, not staleness handling. Spec deviation confirmed \u2014 checkUpkeep uses non-reverting _getAssetPrice(asset, false) while performUpkeep uses reverting _getAssetPrice(assetOut, true), breaking the eligibility invariant (SG-002). Attack path requires environmental oracle staleness (heartbeat gap or brief feed outage) rather than a directly attacker-controlled trigger, yielding CONFIRMED_POTENTIAL. MEDIUM severity aligns with 'DoS of core functionality / auction participation blocking' per severity_classification thresholds.",
      "spec_reference": "SG-002"
    }
